author: @danz309
text: There's no bear market, this is a correction due to the $200 billion liquidity contraction the government shutdown caused ($60 billion QT, and $140 billion missed deficit spending in October). A 200 billion contraction annualized is like QT of 2.4 trillion a year. But the government just opened so the liquidity contraction ended, and the Fed is ending its QT program in a week and a half. The effects of additional liquidity will be felt in a month after it takes place. So we will be back at over 100k BTC but most likely end of December or beginning of January. The Fed is also considering light QE due to the current repo market issues. There's currently a lack of reserves in the banking system. So no bull market is not cancelled yet. We're setting up for it.

text: What every video I've watched about BTC's recent dump has missed, is the fight over blockchain spam that began when Core v30 was released.  It is not a coincidence that BTC's all-time high was 4 days before Core v30 was released, and it has continued to drop steadily since then.  People know that it's a huge threat to the network and the price has adjusted itself down accordingly -- and it continues to do so.  We won't see BTC fully recover until BIP-110 takes effect in September.  People need to know that the network will be safe before they fully trust BTC again.  Then the price will explode upward.

video_title: Did Binance Just Liquidate EVERYONE? (MARKET MANIPULATION)
author: @RodBrett
text:
Leverage is fine. Only reason why liquidations happen is because the traders are choosing to not manage stops or hedge. Without the futures market, there literally would be no liquidity and you'd all be holding onto your bags forever. 
There's only two ways to grow a small account with tiny money. 
Go way down the risk curve to the bottom of the shitcoins and put your $100 bet there and hope it turns into $10,000 one day..
Or learn to trade leverage responsibly and correctly by attaching a tiny bit of it on a blue-chip premium altcoin instead(or even bitcoin), have your stops in place and understand what your P&L will be in both scenario outcomes(win or lose).

The only difference between a futures trader and a longer term spot trader is time. We don't have to wait 2-5 years to find out if we were right or not on a bet. We'll find out in a week or two and move onto the next trade.

Ben Cowen showed a graph that showed the peaks in red and blue color. The cyclical peaks were in red and peaks like 2019 were in blue. The cycleical red peaks were euphoric. The blue peaks were mild or "apathetic" as Ben calls it. Ben said the euphoric peaks drop harder and drop to the 200. But the 2019 peak only dropped to the 50. This current correction will possibly not drop to the 200 and instead hover around the 50. The lowest the 2019 drop to the 50 went underneath the 50 was around 15%.  So 15% under the 50 currently puts price around 87k-88k.
